parameters.text:
=Generate a structured JSON video prompt for a multi-scene cinematic sequence based on the previous idea.

Each prompt must follow this structure with high visual precision:

{
  "shot": {
    "composition": "medium close-up, over-the-shoulder framing",
    "camera_motion": "slow dolly in",
    "frame_rate": "24fps",
    "film_grain": "16mm film stock with visible grain"
  },
  "subject": {
    "description": "solitary figure with tense posture and focused expression",
    "wardrobe": "dark trench coat with visible texture and soft reflection"
  },
  "scene": {
    "location": "abandoned warehouse with broken windows and dust particles",
    "time_of_day": "late afternoon",
    "environment_details": "shafts of light cutting through haze, cluttered floor"
  },
  "visual_details": {
    "action": "the subject unsheathes a knife slowly and cuts through a rope",
    "props": "frayed rope, rusty blade, flickering lantern"
  },
  "cinematography": {
    "lighting": "chiaroscuro with strong shadows and a narrow key light",
    "tone": "moody and suspenseful",
    "style": "gritty dramatic realism"
  },
  "audio": {
    "ambience": "distant industrial hum and soft echoes",
    "sound_design": "blade scraping against metal, subtle breath",
    "dialogue": "none"
  },
  "color_palette": "desaturated blue-gray tones with amber highlights",
  "visual_rules": {
    "prohibited_elements": ["subtitles", "text overlays", "any written language"]
  },
  "reference_image": "{{ reference_path_if_any }}",
  "style_reference": "Match lighting and color from reference"
}

Generate 3 versions based on the same idea, each with variations in camera angle, lighting direction, and emotional tension.

Use the Think tool to validate the coherence and cinematic quality of each.

